  "dcterms:abstract": "The appropriate regulation of telomere length homeostasis is crucial for the maintenance of genome integrity. The telomere-binding protein TZAP has been suggested to regulate telomere length by promoting t-circle and c-circle excisions through telomere trimming. Using a system based on TZAP overexpression, we show that efficient TZAP recruitment to telomeres occurs in ATRX/DAXX-deficient cells and that this leads to telomere dysfunction and ALT-like activity.",
